cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DB

This paper presents a set of real-world, production-scale DNNs for personalized recommendation and discusses the performance metrics for evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the implications of these workloads on system design and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on content ranking and recommendation, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
